Spokesman for the Coalition of United Political Parties (CUPP) Ugochinyere Ikenga, has assured the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) that his acceptance and popularity will secure victory for the party at the Ideato North/Ideato South Federal Constituency election. He said as the PDP candidate, he said he will stop at nothing to return the Constituency to the PDP, assuring that the current representative, didn’t meet the yearnings of the people. Ikenga clinched the PDP ticket after a.keenly contested primaries.   Sen Otu wins APC guber primary in Cross River     And God decided to show up, by Femi Adesina     Sen. Uba Sani wins Kaduna APC Gov ticket   In his remarks, shortly after being declared winner, the CUPP spokesman thanked the delegates for reposing confidence in him, assuring that as the.party’s candidate, he will work hard to return the Federal Constituency to the Peoples Democratic Party after over 10 years. Ikenga also extended hand of fellowship to his opponents to rally round him and the party as the victory was for all of Ideato nation and not just him. He enjoined them to close ranks as they work towards taking the Constituency for the party. The exercise was monitored by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC).